INSERT INTO plants VALUES(1,'Swiss Cheese Plant','Monstera Deliciosa','One of the most recognisable houseplants is the Monstera Deliciosa, its unique leaves often seen in prints. A native to the tropical rainforests of Southern Mexico and Panama. This plant enjoys warm and humid conditions. Leaves can grow exceptionally large.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/files/P24MonsteraMP-CoolGreyCapri_1800x1800.jpg?v=1736336527','HIGH','HIGH','WARM','HIGH','BOTH','2025-05-26 04:19:30','2025-05-27 08:34:46');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(2,'Kentia palm','Howea Forsteriana','An easy to care for plant with fresh green leaves that fan out. The Kentia Palm can tolerate low light. It is one of the best plants for improving air quality, removing toxins such as formaldehyde, ammonia and carbon monoxide from the air, this makes it an ideal home and office plant. It is native to Lord Howe Island in Australia.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/products/BD_H_M_Kentia_1080x.jpg?v=1676657024','MODERATE','LOW','MODERATE','LOW','BOTH','2025-05-27 08:19:46','2025-05-27 08:19:46');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(3,'Money Tree','Pachira Aquatica','We can''t promise that this plant will grow you money (sorry!) but it''s said that the Money Tree will bring you prosperity and positive energy - the good luck is interwoven in the twisted trunks. This Pachira is paired with our perfectly fitting ceramic, Capri pot.  Many businesses like to position their tree by the cash register for good luck. If money''s not your motive, still reach for the stars, as in the wild, these trees have been known to grow up to 59 feet tall.  Drainage is key - although this tree appreciates moisture, don''t let it sit in puddles of water. It also has an appetite for a balanced fertiliser, but only needs it once a month.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/files/W12PACHIRA-COOLGREYCAPRI-RIGHTSIZE_EDITED_1800x1800.png?v=1724761627','HIGH','MODERATE','MODERATE','MODERATE','INDOOR','2025-05-27 08:22:18','2025-05-27 08:22:18');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(4,'Fishbone Cactus','Epiphyllum anguliger','This eye-catching cactus originates from the rainforest of Mexico and has uniquely shaped long, flat stems resembling (you guessed it) a fishbone! The stems start by growing upright but as they grow longer, they will eventually trail down over your stylish ceramic ribbed pot. This is an epiphytic plant meaning it grows aerial roots, this is because, in its natural environment, the fishbone would anchor to a host plant.  These pots are glazed and finished by hand, which means you may notice some minor imperfections such as small surface bubbles or light variations in colour. ','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/files/ribbedwhite-fishbone_1800x1800.jpg?v=1745398168','LOW','LOW','COLD','LOW','BOTH','2025-05-27 08:23:59','2025-05-27 08:23:59');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(5,'Peace Lily','Spathiphyllum wallisii','The characteristic white bloom of the Peace Lily is said to be how it received its common name, representing the white flags of a ceasefire. This is recognised as one of the best plants for improving air quality, known to help remove nasty toxins from the air. The flowers of a Peace Lily are in fact specially adapted leaves called a bract. It is native to South America and from the same family as a Flamingo Flower.  An ideal plant for anyone new to plant parenting, this plant makes the perfect gift in its stylish ceramic ribbed pot. Water your plant regularly, when its soil feels dry but reduce your watering schedule in the colder winter months - the Peace Lily is far more tolerant of underwatering, than overwatering!  These pots are glazed and finished by hand, which means you may notice some minor imperfections such as small surface bubbles or light variations in colour.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/products/B_D_Houseplants22_020_1800x1800.jpg?v=1741350185','HIGH','HIGH','WARM','MODERATE','INDOOR','2025-05-27 08:24:43','2025-05-27 08:24:43');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(6,'Aspidistra','Cast Iron','This striking plant is native to China and Japan. It has gorgeous tall, dark green, paddle shaped leaves that make a real statement. Super easy to look after, this plant is well known for being able to withstand some neglect giving rise to its common name. This plant works really well in dim corners and corridors and generally those places where other plants may have failed to thrive.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/products/BD_H_M_CastIron_1080x.jpg?v=1700143356','MODERATE','LOW','MODERATE','MODERATE','OUTDOOR','2025-05-27 08:26:44','2025-05-27 08:26:44');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(7,'Ficus Benjamina','Weeping Fig','Naturally found in tropical regions such as India, China, Malaysia and Australia, the Ficus Benjamina or Weeping Fig is a gorgeous plant that has slender, arching branches with glossy dark leaves. This plant is great for air purifying and can remove toxins such as formaldehyde and benzene from the atmosphere.  Elegant and timeless, the classic weeping fig brings a graceful silhouette to your space. Its cascading green foliage adds a natural softness, while its easy-care nature makes it a go-to for both beginners and seasoned plant lovers.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/files/FicusBenjaminaTwilight-016copy_1080x.jpg?v=1746197571','LOW','MODERATE','MODERATE','HIGH','BOTH','2025-05-27 08:28:55','2025-05-27 08:28:55');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(8,'Amstel King','Ficus binnendijkii','With luscious long leaves in rich green tones, this plant stands tall, making a real statement. Unlike other Ficus varities, the Amstel King isn''t fussy about being moved about and won''t shed its leaves as a result - ideal if you like redecorating!  Make sure you give this tree the royal treatment as it is also called the ''Ficus Alii'' - “Alii” means ''king'' in Hawaii, where this plant was first grown commercially.  The Amstel King isn''t a fan of the cold and appreciates a misting every now and then, too. During growing season, feel free to feed him with a small amount of a fertiliser a couple times a month. On the whole, this is a very easy-to-care for plant and will be forgiving of some occasional neglect.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/files/CalatheaBush65cm-232_1080x.jpg?v=1746196780','MODERATE','LOW','WARM','MODERATE','BOTH','2025-05-27 08:33:40','2025-05-27 08:36:05');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(9,'Stromanthe Triostar','Calathea','A native to the jungles of the Amazon region in South America, this is a stunning plant with variegated leaves in a spectrum of shades of pink, green and white. Part of the Calathea family and related to the Prayer Plant.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/files/BD_calathea_triostar_720x.jpg?v=1724247939','MODERATE','HIGH','WARM','MODERATE','INDOOR','2025-05-27 08:39:42','2025-05-27 08:39:42');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(10,'Cacti','Mini Cacti','The Mini Cacti Set is the perfect way to bring a little desert charm into your space without the fuss! These adorable, low-maintenance plants all come in their own unique shape, texture, and personality. Whether displayed together for a striking mini oasis or dotted around your home for a subtle touch of greenery, these little cacti are guaranteed to add effortless style.  Hardy and resilient, they thrive on minimal care, making them ideal for both seasoned plant lovers and total beginners. Just a little sunlight and the occasional sip of water, and they’ll be happy!','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/files/CactiTerracottaMiniSet-370_1080x.jpg?v=1740495737','LOW','LOW','WARM','LOW','BOTH','2025-05-27 08:41:14','2025-05-27 08:41:14');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(11,'Succulent','Echeveria','Mini Succulents are tiny treasures that pack a whole lot of charm. With their plump, rosette-shaped leaves and unique textures, these little beauties are the perfect way to add a touch of nature to any nook, shelf, or desk. Each succulent arrives in a sleek, minimalist pot that complements its understated elegance, ready to brighten up your space with little effort.  Easy to care for and incredibly resilient, these mini plants thrive in bright, indirect light and need only occasional watering, just let the soil dry out between drinks. Whether you’re a seasoned plant lover or a newbie, these succulents are perfect for adding a touch of greenery with minimal fuss. ','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/files/BD_mini_succulent_trio_close1_720x.jpg?v=1742202119','MODERATE','LOW','MODERATE','LOW','INDOOR','2025-05-27 08:42:22','2025-05-27 08:42:22');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(12,'Oxalis Triangularis','Purple Shamrock','This rare and sought-after established Oxalis Triangularis plant has gorgeous distinctive purple leaves that will close at night and open again in the morning. This wonderful plant also has edible flowers.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/products/BD_H_M_583Webedit_1080x.jpg?v=1710153135','MODERATE','HIGH','MODERATE','MODERATE','INDOOR','2025-05-27 08:44:36','2025-05-27 08:44:36');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(13,'Peach Anthurium','Flamingo Flower','','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/files/Beards-Daises-27.9.220243copy_1080x.jpg?v=1712129894','MODERATE','HIGH','MODERATE','MODERATE','INDOOR','2025-05-27 08:45:32','2025-05-27 08:45:32');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(14,'White Orchid','Phalaenopsis','A very popular houseplant that offers a display of exotic white blooms. The Moth Orchid is naturally found in the tropical regions of Australia and South-eastern Asia. It is thought they were given that name because their blooms resemble moths in flight. In their natural environment these plants are epiphytic meaning they will attach their roots to trees or rocks. Don’t be scared by the exotic look of this plant, with some regular care you will be rewarded with gorgeous blooms!','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/products/IMG_0327_fba10d6a-8014-4e5a-be95-dd3d1520b957_720x.jpg?v=1663773998','MODERATE','HIGH','MODERATE','MODERATE','INDOOR','2025-05-27 08:46:37','2025-05-27 08:46:37');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(15,'Monaco Orchid','Orchidaceae','This uniquely coloured Orchid is also known as the jewel orchid - and we completely understand why! The gorgeous peachy orange tones of its delicate petals are a real show-stopper and feel incredibly luxe. Comes with a perfectly fitting white ceramic pot to sit within.  Native to the tropical regions of South East Asia, it''s an epiphytic - meaning that you''ll find it growing on trees. It''s beautiful latin name comes comes from the ancient Greek translation of ''like a butterfly''. We couldn''t think of a more appropriate description of this plants delicate beauty!  Easy to care for, the Monaco Orchid appreciates plenty of bright light - but don''t let it sit in direct sunlight. You won''t need to water this beauty too often either, instead it prefers its soil to fully dry out between waterings.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/files/BD_MONACO_ORCHID_1080x.jpg?v=1696934433','LOW','MODERATE','MODERATE','LOW','INDOOR','2025-05-27 08:48:52','2025-05-27 08:48:52');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(16,'String of Hearts','Ceropegia Woodii','This hardy houseplant has very pretty heart shaped foliage, hence the name! This is a vine type plant which grows long, wispy trails. Native to South Africa, Swaziland and Zimbabwe. A low maintenance houseplant that is good for new plant parents.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/products/B_D2_Day-1_20_RESIZED_1080x.jpg?v=1741872023','LOW','MODERATE','WARM','LOW','BOTH','2025-05-27 08:50:20','2025-05-27 08:50:20');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(17,'Rubber Plant','Ficus Elastica Robusta','Part of the fig family this is a hardy, fast growing houseplant that can fill space quickly. This plant has broad dark green, glossy foliage and in its natural environment in southeast Asia can grow to over 30m tall.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/products/BD_H_M_231_a859ecdb-9305-45f7-bb9e-4ef95de9a920_1080x.jpg?v=1675260237','LOW','MODERATE','COLD','LOW','BOTH','2025-05-27 08:51:44','2025-05-27 08:51:44');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(18,'Fiddle-Leaf Fig','Ficus Lyrata','Enjoy the beauty of the classic Fiddle Leaf Fig. The fiddle-shaped leaves of this houseplant are well-loved, and for good reason - they''re gorgeous! Native to the rainforests of western and central Africa, this plant makes a great visual impact with its large green leaves. While this plant does require some maintenance to keep happy, it''s more than worth it when you''re rewarded with such beautiful green leaves. Fiddle Leaf Figs are sensitive to new environments, so give it a little while to settle into its new home. You''ll want to try your best to create an environment for this plant which mimics it''s natural humid home, so treat it to a weekly misting and keep it warm.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/files/Plant_and_pot_masterArtboard69_720x.jpg?v=1695741540','MODERATE','MODERATE','WARM','MODERATE','BOTH','2025-05-27 08:54:07','2025-05-27 08:54:07');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(19,'Euphorbia Trigona Cactus','African Milk Tree','This unique looking plant may have cactus in its name but it''s actually a succulent that''s native to West Africa, but can also be found in tropical Asia and India. It has unique spines along its stems and small leaves that cover the edges of the stems and stalk. The plant is also known as an African Milk Tree which is given due to the milky white sap that comes out when it is cut or broken. The Euphorbia Trigona Cactus is easy to care for, but remember that it will need dusting to unblock its pores, helping it to breathe. They also have a tendency to be top heavy due to their shallow roots so do expect to support the plant with canes where necessary.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/products/Beards-Daises-27.9.220255copy_1080x.jpg?v=1664961348','LOW','LOW','MODERATE','LOW','BOTH','2025-05-27 08:54:55','2025-05-27 08:54:55');
INSERT INTO plants VALUES(20,'Blue Star Fern','Phlebodium Aureum','An unusual houseplant which has a unique appearance compared to other ferns. Elongated fronds that have a pretty green-blue colour. The blue star fern is an epiphyte meaning it can grow on other trees rather than in the soil. They are naturally found in the tropical rainforests of South America.','https://www.beardsanddaisies.co.uk/cdn/shop/files/bluestarcropped_1080x.png?v=1726743112','MODERATE','MODERATE','MODERATE','MODERATE','BOTH','2025-05-27 08:56:14','2025-05-27 08:56:14');
